# Approach
The first function finds the first occurrence of the target key in the array. It uses a modified binary search, where it updates the ans variable whenever it finds the target and then continues searching in the left half of the array to find the first occurrence.

The last function finds the last occurrence of the target key in the array. Similar to the first function, it uses a modified binary search to update the ans variable whenever it finds the target and then continues searching in the right half of the array to find the last occurrence.

Finally, the searchRange function returns a vector containing the results of the first and last functions, representing the range of occurrences of the target key in the sorted array. If the target is not found, the ans variable remains -1, and the function returns {-1, -1} indicating that the target is not present in the array.

