By Using **Binary Search**  we can able to achieve this solution in logn time ( it is given that array already sorted) 

So by the technique of calculation of **lower bound and upper bound** we calculate the index of target in lower bound area and similarly in upper bound area.

* runs two separate loop for both.
* store the index of target whenever it got.  
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/663e1b29-ae8d-4e38-9953-c0ec3aef464f_1651669334.2044718.png)

**Time complexity - O(nlogn)
Space complexity - O(1)**


