`Algorithm:`
> - Start with a classic Binary search solution
> - Do not stop at the target rather continue traversing to the left side of the list. 
> - Pay close attention to code difference between two binary search: 
			> First-Position Vs Last-Position 
			> Notice the difference in equality "=" sign
> - At the end of first binary search, if the number wasn't found, terminate early and return [-1,-1]
> - Perform second binary search for Last-Position
	> Return results
```
const searchRange = function(nums, target) {
    let firstPosition = -1, lastPosition = -1;
    let lo = 0, hi=nums.length-1; 

    // Search firstPosition
    while(lo<=hi){
        let mid = Math.floor((lo+hi)/2);
        if(nums[mid] >= target) hi = mid-1;
        else lo=mid+1;
    }

    // Check if number exists
    if(nums[lo] !== target) return [-1, -1];
    firstPosition = lo;

    // Reset pointers
    let lo =0, hi=nums.length-1; 

    // Search lastPosition
    while(lo<=hi){
        let mid =  Math.floor((lo+hi)/2);
        if(nums[mid] > target) hi = mid-1;
        else lo=mid+1;
    }
    lastPosition=hi;

    return [firstPosition, lastPosition]
};
```

