**Time Complexity**:O(n)
**Space Complexity**:O(1)

**Approach-2: Binary Search**: Here we use two binary searches to find first and last occurance of target.
```
vector<int> searchRange(vector<int>& nums, int target) {
        vector<int>res = {-1,-1};
        if(nums.size()==0) return res;
        int i=0, j= nums.size()-1;
        // finding the first occurance of target in nums array
        while(i<j){
            int mid = (i+j)/2;
            if(nums[mid] < target)
                i=mid+1;
            else 
                j = mid;
        }
        if(nums[j] == target) res[0] =j;    
        else return res;                // If there is no first occurance, then we directly return res
        j=nums.size()-1;                //again we dont have to initialize i from beginning
        // Finding last occurance of target in nums array
        while(i<j){
            int mid = (i+j)/2+1;        // To make sure that mid is biased towards right, 
            if(nums[mid]<=target)       // so that, it wont stuck at a particular case.
                i = mid;
            else 
                j = mid-1;
        }
        res[1] =j;
        return res;
    }
```
**Time Complexity**:O(log(n))
**Space Complexity**:O(1)

**Note:** There is other approach using STL, making use of inbuilt functions like `lower_bound` and `upper_bound`. But, this is not an ideal way to solve for this problem, many interviewers expect to solve this problem using binary search approach.

