# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
In this question we need to find the starting and ending index of the given target and return an array of {startidx,endidx} and if target is not present return {-1,-1} array.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Explained in the code.

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[] searchRange(int[] nums, int target) {
        int[] arr = new int[2];
        Arrays.fill(arr,-1);
        //elements set to -1 by default
        if(nums.length==1 && nums[0]==target){
            /*if length of given array is 1 and the target is present at
            the 0th index then return {0,0} array.*/
            Arrays.fill(arr,0);
            return arr;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            //finding the starting index of the target
            if(nums[i]==target){
                arr[0] = i;
                break;
            }
        }
        for(int i=nums.length-1;i>=0;i--){
            //finding the last index of the target
            if(nums[i]==target){
                arr[1] = i;
                break;
            }
        }
        return arr;
    }
}
