# Intuition
we have to find the target element and then keep on updating the left and right pointers till we reach the border of the repeating sequence.

# Approach
Make a seperate function which performs normal binary search. but we will call it two times. one for left boundary and one for right boundary. It will accept a boolean variable which will tell the function to search for left boundary or right boundary. 

1. FOR LEFT Boundary -
    - set boolean to true.
    - initialise left and right pointers on boundaries of array.
    - initialise mid pointer inside while loop.
    - initialise a pointer i which will give you the boundary value.
    - perform a simple binary search but when you find the element set i=mid and then keep on updating the right pointer as right=mid-1.
    - then return i.


2. FOR RIGHT boundary - 
    - set boolean to false.
    - initialise left and right pointers on boundaries of array.
    - initialise mid pointer inside while loop.
    - initialise a pointer i which will give you the boundary value.
    - perform a simple binary search but when you find the element set i=mid and then keep on updating the left pointer as left=mid+1.
    - then return i. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
log(n)


# Code
