# Explanation

- If ```total cost of loop > total gas available``` then for sure we'll not be able to complete the loop so return -1.

- Now if the above condition doesn't satisfy means there exist atleast one answer.

- We'll start iterating from the first index, if anywhere in the path we've found ```fuel < 0``` at index "i" means we can't proceed further. So, we have to restart our journey from that very same index(i).
- Now that we have proven in the previous step that we can reach index "i", we have changed our target from the loop to the end index of the array because if we can manage the cost of the last index, we will reach at index "i" by using the fuel of 1st to "i"th index.

