**Intuition:** we can use greedy approach since we just have to check the best option to start.

**Approach:**
From observation, we can see that there's only 2 possible outcomes.
1. Take out total_fuel and total_cost. If total_fuel is less than total_cost, that means this journey is not possible so return -1.
2. Now just check => `gas = [1,2,3,4,5]` and `cost = [3,4,5,1,2]`
3. At i=0, if we do gas[i] - cost[i] i.e 1-3, we get -2. Since it is negative how can we start the journey here. So we will keep going forward until we find a combination whose difference will give us positive fuel. 

**Lets do a DRY RUN =>**
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/af152b07-a9ff-4e98-9985-c630f620374c_1673052445.254524.png)
We see that 3 is the answer for this Input, so lets start at 3. Remember that travel needs gas[i]-cost[i] to be positive.
Here diff is the fuel consumed to reach the next position
1. At i=3, travel_cost = 0 and diff = (4-1) = 3
2. At i=4, travel_cost = 3 + (5-2) = 6
3. At i=0, travel_cost = 6 + (1-3) = 4
4. At i=1, travel_cost = 4 + (2-4) = 2
5. At i=2, travel_cost = 2 + (3-5) = 0
Here we observe that our fuel got over at i=2 and we reached destination i.e i=3 position.

**Brute Force Solution:**
Each time we traverse the whole vector for each position, giving us time complexity of O(N^2).
**Optimised Solution:**
```
class Solution {
public:
    int canCompleteCircuit(vector<int>& gas, vector<int>& cost) {
        int current = 0;
        int total_fuel = 0, total_cost=0;
        int diff = 0;
        int start = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i < gas.size(); i++) {
            total_fuel += gas[i];
        }       
        for(int i = 0; i < gas.size(); i++) {
            total_cost += cost[i];
        }
        // edge case
        if(total_fuel < total_cost) {
            return -1;
        }

        for(int i = 0; i < gas.size(); i++){
            current += (gas[i] - cost[i]);
            if(current < 0){
                start = i + 1;
                current = 0;
            }
        }

        return start;
    }
};
```

**Time Complexity** =>`O(N)`
**Space Complexity** => `O(1)`

