solutions.content:
res : Result index
exgas : Extra Gas we have remaining after reaching each gas station
regas : Required gas 

Consider the following numbers in this format: (Gas at station, Cost to reach next station) for DRY RUN

    1.   2.    3.    4.    5.   6
(7,6) , (8,7) , (5,8) , (11,9) , (7,7) , (6,5)

We will traverse from point 1 to 2, then 2 to 3 and so on.

On every traversal, we can update the extra gas that we have left from the last station, ie,
exgas += gas_at_current_station - distance_to_reach_next_station

The only trick you need to understand here is that :
Once we reach a point where we cannot reach the next station even after using exgas, then the starting position cannot be any previous stations and will be the any of the next stations ONLY. 
So update the exgas as 0, because now we will consider the next station as our starting point.

Then we will simply update the regas (REQUIRED GAS), so that once we reach the end and start traversing from the start to the result index we can simply check the regas and know how much extra gas we would need inorder to do the traversal (since we failed before).

So now we will simply check if adding the current extra gas to the required gas gives the +ve result, showing whether we'll be able to traverse or not.

```
class Solution {
public:
    int canCompleteCircuit(vector<int>& gas, vector<int>& cost) {
        int res = 0;
        int exgas = 0;
        int regas = 0;
        int n = gas.size();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            exgas += (gas[i] - cost[i]);
            if(exgas < 0){
                res = i+1;
                regas += exgas;
                exgas = 0;
            }
        }

        if(regas+exgas >= 0) return res;
        return -1;
    }
};
```

