1. Gas[i] will add to our tank, and cost[i] will substract from our tank.
2. To be able to complete the circuit, one must have this value (gas[i] -cost[i] , lets call it val[i]) always greater than equal (>=) to 0 at each i. 
3. And we can travel only towards right (and then back to beginning index).

**Approach** :

If we assume some middle element (say index 4) is the answer. Then val[4]+ val[5] +..+val[n] + val[0] + va[1] + ... + val[3] is what car circular routes might look like. And at not point should this cumulative sum becomes negative. (or else, this is not the right route , as your tank is empty in between)


( val[4] +.. + val[n] ) = Sum of the first part of our route : must be a positive sum.
And there should be no negative value in this cumulative sum  ( let call it Sum-First-Part)

