### **Please Upvote** :D
---
- Check if `total gas` is lesser than `total cost`, if yes its impossible to travel so return `-1`.
- Else, start moving from the beginning, if `remaining ga`s is lesser than `0` means we can't move further.
- In such case, we put `start` as `i + 1` as it can be our potential position to return.
- Otherwise our gas stays collected in `remainingGas` and we keep moving further.
- At the end we return `start` because it will keep getting updated to each potential start point when remaining gas becomes lesser than `0`.
``` java []
class Solution {
    public int canCompleteCircuit(int[] gas, int[] cost) {
        int totalGas = 0, totalCost = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < gas.length; i++) {
            totalGas += gas[i];
            totalCost += cost[i];
        }

        if (totalCost > totalGas) {
            return -1;
        }

        int remainingGas = 0, start = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < gas.length; i++) {
            remainingGas += (gas[i] - cost[i]);
            if (remainingGas < 0) {
                remainingGas = 0;
                start = i + 1;
            }
        }

        return start;
    }
}

// TC: O(n + n) => O(n)
// SC: O(1)
```
