- Start moving from the beginning, if `remaining gas` is lesser than `0` means we can't move further.
- In such case, we put `start` as `i + 1` as it can be our potential position to return.
- Otherwise our gas stays collected in `remainingGas` and we keep moving further.
- Meanwhile keep calculating `extra gas` for the whole journey, if its lesser than `0` means we cant complete our journey so return `-1`.
- Else return `start` (it will keep getting updated to each potential start point when remaining gas becomes lesser than `0`).

