solutions.content:
This is an exhaustive approach. First we loop through the entire circut and get the cumulative sum. If it's less than 0, there will not be any index from which we can start. If it's 0 or greater, then there must be at least one index from which we can start.

On pass 2, we start with the assumption that there must be at least one index from which we can start.

Start from index 0, loop forward... If our cumulative sum drops below 0, it means that our start index is incorrect. Furthermore, it means that any index between our start index and the current index are also invalid. (the first index yielded a positive net, but the current index is the "killer" index) -- this means that the correct answer starts later in the list. We move the start index past the current index and reset our tank. If we've exhausted every possibility except for n-1, then the final solution must be n-1.

```
class Solution {
public:

    int canCompleteCircuit(vector<int>& gas, vector<int>& cost) {

        int aCount = gas.size();
        int aTank = 0;
        int aIndex = 0;

        for (aIndex=0;aIndex<aCount;aIndex++) {
            aTank += gas[aIndex] - cost[aIndex];
        }

        //If we cannot complete the circuit with a positive tank,
        //then there is no index from which we can start.........
        if (aTank < 0) { return -1; }

        aTank = 0;
        int aStartIndex = 0;
        for (aIndex=0;aIndex<(aCount-1);aIndex++) {

            aTank += gas[aIndex] - cost[aIndex];

            if (aTank < 0) {
                //The previous start index we've attempted from has miffed.
                //Since we were positive at said starting index, it also holds
                //true that the indices between the start index and the current
                //index would also get the tank below 0... E.G. the index we JUST ARRIVED AT
                //is the index in which our tank goes negative. So there must be a later index
                //where our net is higher...
                aStartIndex = aIndex + 1;
                aTank = 0;
            }
        }

        return aStartIndex;
    }
};
```

